╕This is not the end; it is not even the beginning of the end
but perhaps, the end of the beginning 
For my mum - my best friend and role model
Anita Shaw 1948 2008"╙
╖IN LOVING MEMORY OF
MUM, LILLIAN GRACE PINFOLD (NEE BOREHAM)
BORN INWORTH STREET, BATTERSEA ON JUNE 4TH 1914
PASSED AWAY OCTOBER 7TH 2008
AND GREATLY MISSED BY ALL"╙
╖In fond memory of
Our Founder Mrs June Mackay
Our Chairman John Perry
and Secretary Mrs Louise Perry (nee Conner)
from the members of the Brixton Dog Training Club"╝
╚[{"URL":"/image/b26ff6d56892d3ce0e1e82b40a32eaee3ac419cb","licence":"CC BY-SA 4.0","media_type":"inscription","sha1":"b26ff6d56892d3ce0e1e82b40a32eaee3ac419cb","width":3840,"height":2160},{"URL":"/image/a0b64c3d3497c6547bd72866c8a910400f9eb0dc","licence":"CC BY-SA 4.0","media_type":"inscription","sha1":"a0b64c3d3497c6547bd72866c8a910400f9eb0dc","width":7296,"height":5472},{"URL":"/image/4bf1e2796af20ccbaa136588a8e9492cbc6e91c0","licence":"CC BY-SA 4.0","media_type":"view","sha1":"4bf1e2796af20ccbaa136588a8e9492cbc6e91c0","width":7296,"height":5472}]"╠
╝To Baby Angelina
Our Beautiful angel, Our hearts are filled with sorrow for having left us so soon
We love you; Miss you every moment of everyday
Mum. Dad. Sister & Family"╡
╞DAVID BUCKNELL (DJB) 1939 - 2004
Bon viveur, raconteur, tin collector extraordinaire
was born to retire and went to Paradise by way of
Kensal Green (and a hostelry or two!)"Ё
╟Stranger Stop Here and Rest Your Thoughts on
LOVELY LISA GRAYLEY
Mum to Pretty Lottie, Sweetheart to Paul and Beautiful Friend to
Those of Us Who Knew Her "Sweet Dreams Sis""╦
╣Eve Louise Boundy
15th July 2014
If ever there is tomorrow when we're not together...there is something you
must always remember. You are braver than you believe, stronger than you
seem and smarter than you think. But the most important thing is
even if we're apart... I'll always be with you
A.A. Milne"╨
╥In Loving Memory of
Basil Kenneth Drake
15th March 1931 to 9th April 1998
Who brought his funfairs to the borough for over 40 years
and helped to raise money for various charities"╬
╩Mary Zammit
2nd May 1923 - 26th November 2014
Your life was a blessing your memory treasured every day
An amazing Mum, Nan & Great Grandma
Peter Paul Zammit
7th May 1922 - 10th May 2012
A wonderful dad, grandad & great grandad. In memory of all
the happy times spent here in this park with your grandchildren"©
